Outstanding color and registration on this well-centered card. Extremely tough card, with only 73 copies graded between PSA & SGC and a single 4.5 being the highest graded copy. TRADED. Thanks!

[url=https://flic.kr/p/2o8QT6M][img]https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/52597294187_5256469eb3_z.jpg[/img][/url] [url=https://flic.kr/p/2o8UJfe][img]https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/52598044849_1b0a2a4431_z.jpg[/img][/url]

Got it, thanks.

73 seems like a lot for a somewhat obscure set, so was a little thrown by the "only 73" comment.

Sorry, thought 73 was a mistake.

Rob
Johnson was probably released in all three years, 1914, 1915, and 1916. Good luck with the sale. One of the first pre-war cards I bought at a card show in the 70's was a T213-2 WaJo.
